channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Elite matchmakers—with fees up to $300K—are coaching clients on how to navigate the dating world: It gets tricky for women over 40, experts say
item.description: Matchmakers can help clients avoid the time sink of funneling online or app-based profiles into possible dates.

item.title: Alaska Airlines, flight attendants reach 'record' tentative labor deal
item.description: Alaska's flight attendants' tentative agreement ends a drought of new contracts for cabin crews that have been seeking pay raises for years.

item.title: Bullish bets on top-performing stocks like Nvidia hit a record high this week
FDA OKs first menthol e-cigarettes, drawing criticism from parent groups who say the agency has ‘failed American families’
item.description: The FDA authorized four menthol e-cigarettes from NJOY, the vaping brand recently acquired by tobacco giant Altria, which also makes Marlboro cigarettes.

item.title: Tesla internal data shows company has slashed at least 14% of workforce this year
item.description: Tesla internal records viewed by CNBC suggest the company employs just over 121,000 people, including temporary workers.

item.title: Trump Media expects nearly $70 million from move that helped cause stock’s skid
Nvidia dethroned as world’s most valuable company after just a few days on top as $220 billion selloff sends it to third place
item.description: Nvidia’s market cap was about $3.1 trillion on Friday, lower than Apple Inc. at $3.2 trillion and Microsoft Corp. at $3.3 trillion.

item.title: Wall Street is set to wrap up a strong first half with a key inflation report on deck
item.description: The S&P 500 has advanced to all-time highs this year on the strength and promise of artificial intelligence, as well as the easing of pricing pressures.

item.title: Hospital operator Ardent Health Partners files for IPO
How do you pronounce ‘Nvidia’? Here’s how to say the $3 trillion company’s name, which has mythological roots
item.description: The first “Nvidia” was Invidia, the Roman goddess of envy.

item.title: Apple Intelligence won't launch in EU in 2024 due to antitrust regulation, company says
item.description: Apple Intelligence and two other features won't be available in the European Union when they launch later in 2024, due to interoperability rules in the DMA.

item.title: Car dealers go ‘old school’ as cyberattack forces some services back to paper
Malaysia’s China-friendly stance is a bid to get its biggest trading partner to help keep the economy stable: ‘You can’t be choosy’
item.description: China and Malaysia agreed to a dozen new deals during China Premier Li Qiang’s trip to the Southeast Asian country earlier this week.

item.title: Regulators hit Citigroup, JPMorgan Chase, Goldman Sachs and Bank of America over living will plans
item.description: The living wills are a key Federal Reserve and FDIC exercise mandated in the aftermath of the 2008 global financial crisis.

item.title: Why Trump is getting political ‘upside’ from his crypto reversal
